@skillful101 depending on set up, a heli like this will do about 100-120mph straight and level.  It can go faster in a dive but obviously not for a very long period of time. Watch this video to see a heli do about 165mph coming out of a dive:
watch?v=-wsKRFXuiWE
You can&#39;t go too fast with an RC heli, though. Something called &quot;Retreating blade stall&quot; happens, and things get ugly. I&#39;ve witnessed it a few times on these helicopters and they were only doing 125 or so.

@oasiac I can bet money that this is not a case of reversible pitch!
He was doing barrel rolls, and at 2000-3000rpm (whatever it is for the copter) the blades would snap off if you change the rotation...

Nevertheless, I have no clue how he&#39;s doing it!

Reminds me of a conversation I had with an instructor of mine that was a retired USAF test pilot.  We were discussing the delays in the now defunct Comanche Helicopter program. 

&quot;What you have to understand is that with fixed wing aircraft, we can predict behavior with 95% accuracy before we ever cut metal, but with helicopters, we are really just making educated guesses.&quot;

Complex stuff.
